==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[þymel|þȳmel]]'', corresponding to ''[[thumb]]'' + ''[[-le]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈθɪmbəl/}}
*{{audio|en-us-thimble.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪmbəl|-ɪmbəl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[pitted]], now usually [[metal]], [[cap]] for the [[finger]]s, used in [[sewing]] to [[push]] the [[needle]].
# A similarly shaped [[socket]] in [[machinery]].
# A [[thimbleful]].
# {{nautical}} Any of various metal [[ring]]s used in a ship's [[rigging]]

